Noel Chukwuemeka Okorougo, the facilitator of a ground-breaking  Nike deal for the then Nigeria Football Association(NFA)  in the 1990s,  has  reportedly  died  at 69. His brother, Ujunwa Okorougo broke the sad news at the weekend, saying his elder brother fought bravely but lost the battle to cancer in Switzerland on  June 8.   2023 AFCON Qualifiers:  Peseiro eyes second win against Sao…     Mauritius 2022 : Minister commends Team Nigeria ‘s…     Mikel rewards youngsters at Back2Base Talent Hunt   It would be recalled that shortly after the USA ’94 World Cup where Nigeria emerged joint best entertaining team with Brazil and placed 5th  in the world FIFA ranking, Okorougo marketed Nigeria to Nike who signed a huge contract as Nigeria’s kit sponsors. The then NFA  under late Air Sampson Omeruah   earned huge money from the contract as adequate supply of kits was tremendous and all Nigerian teams appeared in dazzling  colours in their matches especially at the Atlanta Olympic Games where the soccer team won the historic  gold. Okorougo was also  the brain  behind  some of the big friendly matches Nigeria played at the time.